{"page_content": "2.  Content  Head  Overview  \nDue  to  ongoing  performance  concerns,  the  Content  Head  has  been  assigned  an  \nexpanded\n \nrole\n \nwithin\n \nthe\n \neditorial\n \nworkflow.\n \nThe\n \nfollowing\n \nprocedures\n \napply.\n \n \n \nAll\n \ncoordination\n \nbetween\n \neach\n \nstage\n \nor\n \nprocess\n \nmust\n \nbe\n \nhandled\n \nby\n \nassigned\n \nmembers.\n \n \n2.1  Content  Proposal  Stage  \u25cf  Before  any  writing  begins,  the  writer  must  propose  the  content  idea  to  the  \nContent\n \nTeam\n \nHead\n \nor\n \nthe\n \nCEO\n \nin\n \nthe\n \ndesignated\n \nplatform/channel\n  \u25cf  The  writing  process  commences  only  after  the  Content  Head  or  the  CEO  \napproves\n \nthe\n \nproposal.\n  \n2.2  Post-Draft  Review  \u25cf  After  the  drafting  stage  and  before  fact-checking  begins,  the  workflow  \ncoordinator\u2014or\n \nthe\n \nwriter\n \nthemselves\n \nif\n \nno\n \ncoordinator\n \nis\n \nassigned\u2014must\n \nreport\n \nthe\n \ndraft's\n \nstatus\n \nto\n \nthe\n \nContent\n \nHead.\n  \u25cf  The  Content  Head  will  then  review  the  raw  article,  conducting  a  review  that  \nmust\n \ncover\n \nat\n \nminimum:\n \nstructural\n \ncompleteness,\n \nfactual\n \nsource\n \nverification,\n \nand\n \ntonal\n \nconsistency\n \nwith\n \norganizational\n \nstandards.\n \nThe\n \nspecific\n \ncriteria\n \nwithin\n \nthese\n \ncategories\n \nare\n \nto\n \nbe\n \ndetermined\n \nby\n \nthe\n \nContent\n \nHead.\n  \u25cf  No  article  may  proceed  to  the  following  stages  before  this  review  is  \ncompleted.\n  \u25cf  All  assessments  performed  at  this  stage  will  be  recorded  and  evaluated  \nduring\n \nthe\n \nmonthly", "metadata": {"producer": "Skia/PDF m149 Google Docs Renderer", "creator": "PyPDF", "creationdate": "", "title": "Editorial Override", "source": "FactHubMyanmar_EditorialWorkflowUpdate.pdf", "total_pages": 4, "page": 2, "page_label": "3", "author_or_company": "FACT HUB MY